	   <a name=99859085154609></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99859085154609><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99859085154609>High Lvl Wiz gear?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99859085154609#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 23rd 2:20 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am a lvl 27 DE Wiz. I am wondering what some of the gear that high lvl Wizards use? I put as many points into Int as I could, so I only need an additional 65 points to get it to 200. Looking at some of the high end uber items out there, I could theoreticly do this with 3 items. What type of gear do you guys use?<br><br>Currently I use;<br>Blackened Crystiline Robe<br>Staff of the Wheel<br>Stien of Maggok<br>Black Lace sash<br>Froglock Skin Mask<br>Polished bone hoop<br>Batskull Earing<br>Gold star Necklace (+4)<br>Starrose rings x2<br>Bracelets of woven grass x2<br>Cloak of the Forlorn<br><br>My Int is currently 186, and there are several items I have in mind to get to 200. But then what? I image I'll then focus on + mana and +agility. I am just curious as to what more experienced wizards use.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=99901325996508></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99901325996508><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99901325996508>RE: High Lvl Wiz gear?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99901325996508#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=15234><span id=Scholar>Mahatma</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>55 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 28th 11:40 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.28]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It depends on how you like to play your wizzy.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a DE, if you like to group, focus on Int, Mana, Str, Agi.  You already have high agility, but you can't really carry much in the way of loot.  Your primary focus is your effectiveness in a group in this case, so you need to get your mana as high as you can.  When you can't find an item within your price range or ability to camp that increases Int or Mana, go for Str and Agi.<br><br>If you like to solo, Go with max Int, Agi at LEAST over 100, then mana and str.  Solo, you aren't going to be able to camp many mobs that drop much in the way of loot, but you will be able to gain exp faster.  You focus on Agi more than Mana, in this case, because there is no one between the mob and you.  Over 100 Agi, and you start to get diminishing returns on your AC.  I have heard that Dex will affect your ability to recover when interrupted, but I don't know for sure.  It is entirely possible that unless you're quad kiting, you will go through a full bar of mana for every 2 or 3 kills.<br><br>You may also consider partnering with a Druid.  The way you do that is the druid snares, and you both AE nuke once the mobs are in a tight pack.  Quad kiting is amazingly mana efficient since you're dealing almost the amount of damage you could deal to a single target to several with not too much more mana.  One bar of mana, used this way, can kill 4+ mobs (depending on size).<br><br>Thunderous Silenc<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

