	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, I am a newbie but I do have some information you might find useful.&nbsp;&nbsp;I played a Dark Elf wizard that was a worshipper of the Burning Prince (Solusek Ro).  He wasn't KoS in neither of the Freeports, dubious to everyone.  I got faction up with merchants up to amiable by doing the Janam's and Rebby's note quest for the rogues (over and over and over). And you can get faction up with the Knights of Truth by killing lots of orcs or doing the good version of the orc belts.  And FP militia will go up with the evil orc belt quest. You can get faction up with the Arcane Scientists by handing a lady illegible cantrips from casting orc mobs. Also, if you want to sell stuff, there is a secret entrance outside W FP gate with a Dark Elf vender. I can't explain it so your best bet to find it is askind another Dark Elf (How I found it). I really liked playing a Dark Elf wizard, they have really nice vision by the way.  Though now I'm playing a High Elf wizard, because just thinking of how many other places I would be KoS scares me.  And for a newbie, you usually try to stay out of trouble. Don't make that stop you from being a Dark Elf wizard though, because you can avoid lots of places (or so I heard), and there's most likely always a way to get your faction up. Goodluck, I hope this post helped.  But if the information here is somewhat off, don't take it out on me.  I haven't played everquest very long, and this wizard is my first casting class.<br>---- Arkainium ----<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
